VScholarly violin recital
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe premises of Sadguru Brahma Sri Ramadootha Mandiram witnessed a scintillating violin solo rendered by AIR staffer and noted exponent of carnatic music Mutnuri Srinivasa Narasimha Murty. He was accompanied ably on another violin by his wife Pantula Rama and on mridangam by Akashvani staffer Dhanwada Dharmarao.The twelfth in the series of concerts organised annually in memory of noted connoisseur of carnatic music Bhamidipati Kameswari by her son Dr. Vallabha Sastry (Vice Principal, MIMS, Nellimarla) and grandson, noted Vainika Dr. Kanakadurga Prasad (member, teaching faculty, MIMS), it was organised last Saturday by Sangeetha Kala Samithi.The highlights of the two-and-a-half hour concert were the expansive expatiation ofBantureethi(Hamsanadam) withswaraminChaturasramandTrisramin the fast tempo andChaturasramin super fast tempo (measuring 64 letters per cycle of thethalam) and the eruditely structuredpallaviinTrisra TriputainBilhariembellished with scholarly elaboration of the raga concluded with similarthanam.The suffix ofswarakalpanareplete with a variety ofgathiandyathipatterns shifting into ragamalika &#8212;Hamsanandi,Darbari KaanadaandVarali&#8212; executed also in the reverse order marked the grand finale of the evening.Notable among the other items he played wereVallabhanayakasya(Begada) andGurulekha(Gowri Manohari) with ragam and swaram andMayamma(Aahiri) with ragam.
